In some cases, the authors themselves are the distributors of their poems. Thus, the main characteristics of the kurdel genre are:

Spoken language (informal)
Use of humor, irony and sarcasm
Various topics: Brazilian folklore, religious figures, ignoramuses, politicians, historical episodes, social reality, etc.
The presence of rhyme, metrics and oral form [4]. A brochure of this type appeared in the Middle Ages around the 11th-12th centuries. With the invention of the printing press (1450), this literature, which had previously been oral and read by jockeys and minstrels, began to be published on ordinary paper leaflets.